Their names are these:
the Avenlifius, at Dublin;
1 the Banna runs through Ulster;
2 the Moadus, through Connaught ;
3 the Slichenis and Samarius, through Kenelcunnill ;
4 the Modarnus and Phinnus, through Kenel­ eonia;
5 and the Saverennus and Luvius, through Cork.
