It is a remarkable circumstance, or rather a miracle, concerning Lanthoni, that, although it is on every side sur­ rounded by lofty mountains, not stony or rocky, but of a soft nature, and covered with grass, Parian stones are frequently found there, and are called free-stones, from the facility with which they admit of being cut and polished ;
and with these the church is beautifully built.
It is also wonderful, that when, after a diligent search, all the stones have been removed from the mountains, and no more can be found, upon another search, a few days afterwards, they re­ appear in greater quantities to those who seek them.
