The constable and his wife were taken prisoners, with many others, a few persons only escaping, who had sheltered themselves in the principal tower.
With the exception of this stronghold, the enemy violently seized and burned everything;
and thus, by the righteous judgment of God, the crime was punished in the very place where it had been committed.
